  "text": "The correntropy algorithm is known to have the immunity to impulsive noise as well as the ability to compensate for the channel distortion from multipath fading [CITATION_1] . However, it has a disadvantage of the heavy computational complexity due to the double summation operations in [CITATION_2] or (7) at each iteration time. This computational burden prevents its implementation in wireless sensor networks demanding power and cost efficiency. Aiming at the efficient implementation of the correntropy algorithm, a method of reducing the computational complexity of the correntropy algorithm is proposed in the following subsection.",
